    {
      "date": "2026-06-26",
      "session": 1,
      "question_id": 4,
      "type": "grammar",
      "knowledge_point": "modal_verbs",
      "label": "语法题",
      "stem": "—Is that Mr. Wang knocking at the door? —It ______ be him. He has gone to Beijing on business and won't return until next week.",
      "options": [
        "A. must",
        "B. might",
        "C. can't",
        "D. could"
      ],
      "correct_answer": "C",
      "student_answer": "B",
      "explanation": "本题考查情态动词表推测的用法。根据后文'He has gone to Beijing'（他去北京出差了）可知，敲门的人'不可能'是王老师，表示有把握的否定推测用can't（不可能）。must表示肯定推测'一定是'；might和could表示'可能是'，语气较弱，均不符合语境。解题关键：根据客观事实进行逻辑推理，确定是有把握的否定判断。"
    },
    {
      "date": "2026-06-26",
      "session": 1,
      "question_id": 10,
      "type": "cloze",
      "knowledge_point": "cloze_general",
      "label": "完形填空",
      "stem": "(10)______",
      "options": [
        "A. for",
        "B. with",
        "C. of",
        "D. by"
      ],
      "correct_answer": "A",
      "student_answer": "B",
      "explanation": "本题考查固定短语搭配。be responsible for是固定搭配，意为'对...负责'，后接名词或动名词。句意：第一组负责收集可回收垃圾。with、of、by均不与responsible构成此含义的搭配。"
    },
    {
      "date": "2026-06-26",
      "session": 1,
      "question_id": 15,
      "type": "reading",
      "knowledge_point": "word_guessing_context",
      "label": "阅读理解",
      "stem": "What does the word 'sacrificing' in Paragraph 1 probably mean?",
      "options": [
        "A. giving up",
        "B. enjoying",
        "C. increasing",
        "D. changing"
      ],
      "correct_answer": "A",
      "student_answer": "B",
      "explanation": "本题是词义猜测题。根据上下文语境，许多学生认为'牺牲'睡眠时间能帮助取得好成绩，但实际上这是错误的。sacrifice意为'牺牲、放弃'，与give up（放弃）意思最接近。enjoy（享受）、increase（增加）、change（改变）均不符合语境。猜词题可通过同义/反义关系、上下文逻辑（此处有转折However）和构词法来解题。"
    }
  ]
